definition.value: A disaccharide derivative that is alpha-mannobiose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 of each mannose residue has been substituted by a methyl group.
A phosphatidylethanolamine in which the acyl groups at C-1 and C-2 contain 42 carbons in total with 5 double bonds.
A dipeptide obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of L-asparagine with the amino group of L-arginine.
A lyxonate that is the conjugate base of L-lyxonic acid, obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group.

A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a branched hexasaccharide made up from one sialyl residue, two galactose residues, one L-fucose residue, one N-acetyl-6-sulfoglucosamine residue and one glucose residue, which at the reducing end is attached to a d18:1/18:0 ceramide moiety via a beta-linkage; commonly known as sialyl 6-sulfo Lewis X.
A pentonic acid resulting from the formal oxidation of the aldehyde group of lyxose to the corresponding carboxylic acid.
A pentonate resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group of a lyxonic acid.
A lyxonate that is the conjugate base of D-lyxonic acid, obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group.
A bile acid that is 5alpha-cholan-24-oic acid carrying an oxo group at position 3 and a hydroxy group at position 7beta.
A 3-hydroxy steroid that is estriol carrying an oxo group at position 6.
A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of trans-sinapic acid with the hydroxy group of 16-hydroxyhexadecanoic acid.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of 16-sinapoyloxypalmitic acid resulting from the deprotonation of the carboxy group.

A quercetin O-glucoside that is quercetin attached to a beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranoside residue at position 3 via a glycosidic linkage.

A sialopentaosylceramide consisting of a branched hexasaccharide made up from one lactamized sialyl residue, two galactose residues, one L-fucose residue, one N-acetyl-6-sulfoglucosamine residue and one glucose residue, which at the reducing end is attached to a d18:1/18:0 ceramide moiety via a beta-linkage; commonly known as lactamized sialyl 6-sulfo Lewis X ganglioside.
A glycosyloxyflavone that is apigenin substituted by a 6-O-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-beta-D-glucopyranoside group at position 7.
An amino acid zwitterion arising from transfer of a proton from the carboxy to the amino group of L-canaline; major species at pH 7.3.

A sialotetraosylceramide consisting of a linear pentasaccharide made up from one lactamized sialyl residue, two galactose residues, one N-acetyl-6-sulfoglucosamine residue and one glucose residue, which at the reducing end is attached to a d18:1/18:0 ceramide moiety via a beta-linkage.

A neoglycolipid consisting of a linear pentasaccharide made up from one lactamized sialyl residue, two galactose residues, one N-acetyl-6-sulfonatoglucosamine residue (with associated sodium cation) and one glucose residue, which at the reducing end is attached glycosidically to a 2-(tetradecyl)hexadecyl group.
A glycoside that is curcumin substituted by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranoside group at position 4'.
A glycoside that is curcumin substituted by a beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-glucopyranoside group at position 4'.

A neoglycolipid consisting of a branched hexasaccharide made up from one lactamized sialyl residue, two galactose residues, onr fucose residue, one N-acetyl-6-sulfonatoglucosamine residue (with associated sodium cation) and one glucose residue, which at the reducing end is attached glycosidically to a 2-(tetradecyl)hexadecyl group.
A glycosyloxyisoflavone that is genistein substituted by a 6-O-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-beta-D-glucopyranoside group at position 7.
A member of the class of chitobioses consisting of N-acetyl-D-glucosamine having a beta-D-glucosaminyl residue attached at the 4-position.

A furofuran that is cis-tetrahydro-1H,3H-furo[3,4-c]furan substituted by a 6-hydroxy-1,3-benzodioxol-5-yl group at position 1S and a 1,3-benzodioxol-5-yl group at position 4S. It is metabolite found in sesame seeds.
The conjugate base of 2-azelaoyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine, obtained by deprotonation of the free carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
The conjugate base of 2-glutaroyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine, obtained by deprotonation of the free carboxy group; major species at pH 7.3.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as 5-oxovaleroyl.
A 2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the acyl group is specified as 9-oxononanoyl.
A beta-D-glucoside that is sesaminol in which the hydroxy group at position 5 is substituted by a beta-D-glucopyranoside group. A metabolite found in sesame seeds.

A disaccharide derivative that is sesaminol in which the hydroxy group at position 5 has been substituted by a 6-O-beta-D-glucopyranosyl-beta-D-glucopyranoside group. It is a metabolite found in sesame seeds.
A monomethoxyflavone that is myricetin in which the hydroxy group at position 7 is substituted by a methoxy group.

A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of caffeic acid with the hydroxy group at position 6 of the terminal glucose residue of quercetin 3-O-beta-D-glucosyl-(1->2)-beta-D-glucoside.

A glycosyloxyflavone that is myricetin 3-O-[beta-D-glucosyl-(1->2)-alpha-L-rhamnoside] in which the terminal glucose residue has been esterified at position 6 by formal condensation with 4-coumaric acid. Identified in Fig. S21 of PMID:29967287.
A hexahydroxy steroidal lactone that is the 20,22-dihydro derivative of ouabagenin.
A monocarboxylic acid anion that is the conjugate base of mupirocin obtained by the deprotonation of the carboxy group; major microspecies at pH 7.3.

A carboxylic ester resulting from the formal condensation of the carboxy group of hydroxy(diphenyl)acetic acid with the hydroxy group of (1S,3R,5R)-3-hydroxy-8lambda(5)-azaspiro[bicyclo[3.2.1]octane-8,1'-pyrrolidin]-8-ylium. Its chloride salt is used to treat overactive bladder.

A member of the class of hydroxyindoles that is melatonin in which the hydrogen at position 2 of the indole ring has been replaced by a hydroxy group. A predominant hydroxylated melatonin metabolite in plants.
